1
00:00:12,012 --> 00:00:14,014
-Good evening.
-Good evening.

2
00:00:14,097 --> 00:00:16,767
{\an8}<i>Terrace House</i> is a show about
six strangers, men and women,

3
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:17,851
{\an8}6 STRANGERS, MEN AND WOMEN,
SHARE A HOUSE.

4
00:00:17,935 --> 00:00:20,145
{\an8}<i>living together, and we observe</i>
<i>how they interact with each other.</i>

5
00:00:20,228 --> 00:00:23,732
{\an8}All that we've prepared is
a beautiful home and automobile.

6
00:00:23,816 --> 00:00:26,068
{\an8}There is no script at all.

7
00:00:26,151 --> 00:00:29,154
{\an8}Many things happened last week.

8
00:00:29,237 --> 00:00:32,240
{\an8}First, there was
Uchi and Minori's very nice date.

9
00:00:32,324 --> 00:00:34,201
{\an8}TATSUYA UCHIHARA, 23 YEARS OLD
MINORI NAKADA, 21 YEARS OLD

10
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:37,120
{\an8}Well, I asked you out because I like you.

11
00:00:37,204 --> 00:00:40,165
{\an8}What do you mean, you like...

12
00:00:40,248 --> 00:00:42,209
{\an8}Oh, I'm so bad with this stuff!

13
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:44,211
{\an8}<i>He told her he liked her.</i>

14
00:00:44,294 --> 00:00:48,215
Minori didn't answer, but was embarrassed,
like, "Oh no, what should I do?"

15
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:51,677
-And Makoto...
-You almost forgot, didn't you?

16
00:00:52,510 --> 00:00:54,597
Ma-ko-to.

17
00:00:54,680 --> 00:00:58,516
He gave Minori sneakers as a present,

18
00:00:58,601 --> 00:01:01,144
and they went for an evening run together.

19
00:01:01,228 --> 00:01:02,896
{\an8}And gave you the shoes.

20
00:01:02,980 --> 00:01:06,900
{\an8}So, until the season is over,
I wanted to close the gap between us.

21
00:01:06,984 --> 00:01:09,612
{\an8}After the season, when I have more time,

22
00:01:09,695 --> 00:01:11,989
{\an8}maybe we can go somewhere.

23
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:13,991
{\an8}That's what I was thinking.

24
00:01:14,074 --> 00:01:15,117
{\an8}MAKOTO HASEGAWA, 21 YEARS OLD

25
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:19,079
{\an8}He said a line that will go down
in <i>Terrace House</i> history.

26
00:01:19,162 --> 00:01:21,164
"And gave you the shoes."

27
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:27,254
The way things ended
for Yuki and Yuriko...

28
00:01:27,337 --> 00:01:30,465
-That was shocking, right?
-It was shocking.

29
00:01:30,548 --> 00:01:34,094
{\an8}You remember how I once told you about
how I broke up with my ex?

30
00:01:34,177 --> 00:01:36,388
{\an8}I haven't been able to forget him.

31
00:01:36,471 --> 00:01:39,474
{\an8}I think I should take the initiative
and call him,

32
00:01:39,557 --> 00:01:41,769
{\an8}and tell him I miss him.

33
00:01:41,852 --> 00:01:42,936
{\an8}That's good.

34
00:01:43,020 --> 00:01:44,688
{\an8}YUKI ADACHI, 28 YEARS OLD
YURIKO HAYATA, 23 YEARS OLD

35
00:01:44,772 --> 00:01:47,357
{\an8}-It's a good day.
-A good day.

36
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:49,276
{\an8}<i>"It's a good day."</i>

37
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:57,993
<i>What a good day</i>

38
00:01:58,786 --> 00:02:03,999
And Mr. Chou would appear and say,
"How about an ending to love like this."

39
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:07,044
You guys are terrible.

40
00:02:08,045 --> 00:02:10,839
Aren't you getting sick of people?

41
00:02:10,923 --> 00:02:13,801
-That's not true, right?
-No, not at all.

42
00:02:13,884 --> 00:02:15,510
Just a little bit more.

43
00:02:16,219 --> 00:02:18,889
That's what a monster would say.

44
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:20,974
"See, humans are no good."

45
00:02:22,142 --> 00:02:24,352
I think I might see a tail behind me.

46
00:02:33,779 --> 00:02:37,574
{\an8}GIRLS AWARD AUDITIONS

47
00:02:47,876 --> 00:02:49,837
Is this your first time
auditioning for a runway show?

48
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:51,421
-Yes, it's my first time.
-Your first?

49
00:02:51,504 --> 00:02:55,300
{\an8}Then imagine
30,000 attendees watching you.

50
00:02:55,383 --> 00:02:56,719
{\an8}TOSHIYA UO
DIVISION DIRECTOR

51
00:02:56,802 --> 00:02:59,054
{\an8}Please walk with that image in mind.

52
00:02:59,972 --> 00:03:02,224
You're entertaining 30,000 people.

53
00:03:16,363 --> 00:03:17,572
What did you think?

54
00:03:20,158 --> 00:03:24,287
The clothes for this show,
Jill by Jill Stuart, are a little...

55
00:03:24,371 --> 00:03:27,332
We have this image of the models

56
00:03:27,415 --> 00:03:30,377
wearing something chic.

57
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:34,422
So that image, and as I mentioned earlier,

58
00:03:34,506 --> 00:03:38,385
30,000 attendees will be watching you
the entire time.

59
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:42,680
So we want your walk to be fun,

60
00:03:42,765 --> 00:03:45,475
and still express our brand.

61
00:03:45,558 --> 00:03:49,229
In that sense, you're still too stiff.

62
00:03:49,312 --> 00:03:52,065
But I hope you work at it.

63
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:55,693
I'll work on it.

64
00:03:55,778 --> 00:03:57,946
-Thank you.
-Thank you very much.

65
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:13,837
She could be good.
She has long limbs.

66
00:04:14,838 --> 00:04:16,673
She's got a clean look.

67
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:21,094
She's still too stiff.

68
00:04:21,178 --> 00:04:24,139
-But the clothes look good on her.
-Yes.

69
00:04:40,322 --> 00:04:43,450
Hello? This is Yuriko.

70
00:04:45,368 --> 00:04:46,870
It's been awhile.

71
00:04:47,745 --> 00:04:50,498
I'm sorry for calling so suddenly.
I'm sorry.

72
00:04:51,624 --> 00:04:56,213
Oh, thank you for the LINE message.

73
00:04:57,630 --> 00:04:59,174
And...

74
00:05:00,926 --> 00:05:02,803
I thought it'd be nice...

75
00:05:04,096 --> 00:05:07,140
to see you again.

76
00:05:07,224 --> 00:05:09,017
Could we meet?

77
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:20,487
-Hey.
-Game?

78
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:23,531
-Can I come in?
-Yeah.

79
00:05:23,615 --> 00:05:25,408
-By yourself?
-Yeah.

80
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:28,661
What's up?

81
00:05:31,957 --> 00:05:34,918
-I wanted to talk to you.
-What is it?

82
00:05:37,087 --> 00:05:39,839
We went running the other day, right?

83
00:05:39,923 --> 00:05:43,218
I've been thinking about stuff since then.

84
00:05:44,094 --> 00:05:48,431
I was wondering about your timing.

85
00:05:49,892 --> 00:05:53,603
I thought if I let things be,

86
00:05:53,686 --> 00:05:56,148
you'd lean toward Uchi.

87
00:05:57,649 --> 00:06:04,197
I'll take that to mean
that you're interested in me.

88
00:06:04,281 --> 00:06:09,369
But the next time we decide to hang out,

89
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:15,458
it's not intended to mean
I'm responding to your feelings toward me.

90
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:18,503
That's how I feel right now.

91
00:06:21,548 --> 00:06:24,509
We got along so well at first.

92
00:06:24,592 --> 00:06:27,220
I said I was interested in you.

93
00:06:28,596 --> 00:06:30,890
I liked you, but...

94
00:06:30,974 --> 00:06:33,185
to be honest...

95
00:06:33,268 --> 00:06:36,479
I had no idea what you were thinking
or what you wanted to do.

96
00:06:36,563 --> 00:06:40,525
You'd say you were going to ask me out,

97
00:06:40,608 --> 00:06:43,695
but wouldn't follow through.

98
00:06:43,778 --> 00:06:46,489
And so I went on a date with Uchi,

99
00:06:46,573 --> 00:06:51,494
but then you got upset,
and wouldn't talk to me.

100
00:06:51,578 --> 00:06:53,621
Well, it wasn't that
you didn't talk to me,

101
00:06:53,705 --> 00:06:55,290
but you were obviously avoiding me.

102
00:06:55,373 --> 00:06:57,875
I wasn't avoiding you.

103
00:06:57,960 --> 00:07:01,004
It was just plain jealousy.

104
00:07:01,088 --> 00:07:02,965
But that happened...

105
00:07:03,048 --> 00:07:06,718
and it would be an overstatement
to say I was disgusted...

106
00:07:08,386 --> 00:07:10,305
but I didn't like it.

107
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:12,890
And so at this time,

108
00:07:12,975 --> 00:07:18,688
I don't want to go out with you again.

109
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,774
So that's where you're at?

110
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:26,279
Got it.

111
00:07:30,825 --> 00:07:32,577
-Sorry to bother you.
-Later.

112
00:07:33,203 --> 00:07:35,080
-Good night.
-Good night.

113
00:08:12,075 --> 00:08:14,744
{\an8}MAKOTO HASEGAWA, 21 YEARS OLD,
