114
00:08:14,995 --> 00:08:17,622
{\an8}MINORI NAKADA, 21 YEARS OLD, MODEL

115
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:20,500
{\an8}YUKI ADACHI, 28 YEARS OLD, TAP DANCER

116
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:23,711
{\an8}MIZUKI SHIDA, 22 YEARS OLD, OFFICE WORKER

117
00:08:24,046 --> 00:08:26,839
{\an8}TATSUYA UCHIHARA, 23 YEARS OLD,
HAIR STYLIST

118
00:08:27,215 --> 00:08:30,343
{\an8}YURIKO HAYATA, 23 YEARS OLD, MED STUDENT,
4TH YEAR AT TEIKYO UNIVERSITY

119
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:42,605
{\an8}-Hey.
-Hey to you.

120
00:08:43,731 --> 00:08:45,983
-Everyone's still awake today?
-Yeah.

121
00:08:46,734 --> 00:08:47,902
I was...

122
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:51,698
talking with Minori downstairs.

123
00:08:51,781 --> 00:08:55,618
I told her we should hang out
after my season ends.

124
00:08:55,702 --> 00:08:58,580
-Yeah, I remember you saying that.
-You asked her out?

125
00:08:58,663 --> 00:08:59,872
But then...

126
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:03,126
she said something about bad timing.

127
00:09:03,210 --> 00:09:04,586
What timing?

128
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:08,631
Us going out after baseball.

129
00:09:08,715 --> 00:09:11,384
But she said she didn't want to.

130
00:09:11,468 --> 00:09:13,303
-She rejected you?
-Yeah, she said no.

131
00:09:13,386 --> 00:09:15,305
Really? Why?

132
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:19,517
She knows I like her
but can't reciprocate, or something.

133
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:22,270
She said something like that.

134
00:09:22,354 --> 00:09:25,732
She didn't say it outright,
but I guess she dumped me.

135
00:09:26,858 --> 00:09:28,776
-Dumped?
-Yeah.

136
00:09:28,860 --> 00:09:32,655
-Without telling her you liked her?
-I never told her.

137
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:35,367
You never clearly told her your feelings.

138
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:38,786
So I don't think you'd get a clear answer.

139
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:42,124
-So you were wrong?
-I was wrong.

140
00:09:45,377 --> 00:09:49,547
Wow, so Makoto finally admits
that he was wrong.

141
00:09:49,631 --> 00:09:50,840
-I'm glad.
-He was wrong?

142
00:09:50,923 --> 00:09:53,926
-He was wrong.
-But when he was dumped,

143
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:55,262
how did you want him to react?

144
00:09:55,345 --> 00:10:01,559
In the guys' room,
I wanted him to say, "Good luck."

145
00:10:01,643 --> 00:10:03,270
-To Tatsuya.
-Oh, I see.

146
00:10:03,353 --> 00:10:06,356
-"It didn't work out for me, so..."
-"Good luck to you."

147
00:10:06,439 --> 00:10:10,026
Man, you're so thoughtful
to come up with something like that.

148
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:13,446
I was thinking
Uchihara was laughing hysterically inside.

149
00:10:14,906 --> 00:10:16,574
Not hysterically.

150
00:10:16,658 --> 00:10:18,618
No, not laughing hysterically.

151
00:10:18,701 --> 00:10:21,288
I thought he was pinching himself.

152
00:10:23,165 --> 00:10:24,582
Too obvious!

153
00:10:25,667 --> 00:10:28,670
-It was good Minori spoke up.
-It was.

154
00:10:29,296 --> 00:10:35,677
Because she feels his interest,
even though he hasn't said anything,

155
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,680
and she tells him clearly
that she won't reciprocate.

156
00:10:38,763 --> 00:10:42,350
-Why couldn't Yuriko do that, too?
-I knew you would say that.

157
00:10:42,434 --> 00:10:47,147
Even her call to her ex,
wasn't it kind of nasty?

158
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:50,192
-I think it was normal.
-What?

159
00:10:50,275 --> 00:10:52,652
I felt like I was watching a reenactment.

160
00:10:53,903 --> 00:10:57,615
From what she said, it's obvious
that she wants to get back together.

161
00:10:57,699 --> 00:11:02,329
Yeah, for the guy, it's just a matter of
when and if he wants.

162
00:11:02,412 --> 00:11:05,415
It was too obvious.

163
00:11:05,498 --> 00:11:10,170
But if Yuriko was the one
who dumped him in the first place,

164
00:11:10,253 --> 00:11:14,131
then the guy must be happy
that she came back.

165
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:15,925
{\an8}Busy day?

166
00:11:16,008 --> 00:11:19,971
{\an8}Yeah, it was crazy.
A girl from Hokkaido came to see me.

167
00:11:20,722 --> 00:11:22,224
-I was moved.
-Wow, she watches <i>Terrace House?</i>

168
00:11:22,307 --> 00:11:25,685
-Yeah, she saw the show.
-Wow!

169
00:11:25,768 --> 00:11:27,979
-What a nice day.
-Yeah, it was nice.

170
00:11:28,062 --> 00:11:31,441
-You know how we practiced walking?
-Oh yeah, we practiced together.

171
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:33,735
Together? I don't understand.

172
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:38,490
-I was practicing for the audition.
-Yeah, I watched as she practiced.

173
00:11:38,573 --> 00:11:41,243
-It was for Girls Award.
-The one you mentioned before?

174
00:11:41,326 --> 00:11:43,370
-Oh, really?
-You said you were going.

175
00:11:43,453 --> 00:11:47,665
I did, and I passed the audition.

176
00:11:47,749 --> 00:11:50,835
-That's a big one. Congrats! Wow!
-Congratulations!

177
00:11:50,918 --> 00:11:53,796
-That's impressive.
-I have to practice.

178
00:11:54,589 --> 00:11:57,425
Is there something we can do to help?

179
00:11:57,509 --> 00:11:59,886
Hmm, something we can do?

180
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:01,513
Come get your hair done.

181
00:12:01,596 --> 00:12:03,348
-What?
-Come get your hair done.

182
00:12:04,056 --> 00:12:05,642
Treatment and head massage.

183
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:06,893
I want a head massage!

184
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:08,395
-Oh, nice!
-Sure.

185
00:12:08,478 --> 00:12:10,272
I want a head massage!

186
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:15,318
-It's a nice day today.
-Yeah, it's a nice day.

187
00:12:16,403 --> 00:12:19,322
BLAST
DAIKAN-YAMA, TOKYO

188
00:12:19,406 --> 00:12:21,616
{\an8}-Good morning.
-Good morning.

189
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:23,285
{\an8}Let's start the morning meeting.

190
00:12:23,368 --> 00:12:25,745
{\an8}Any announcements?

191
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:27,497
